Subject: [PATCH 018/214] dts/ls2085a-qds: Disable I2C2, I2C3, I2C4 controllers

All I2C devices are connected on I2C1 only on Ls2085AQDS board.

Probe on other controller can lead to error like
"imx-i2c: probe of 2010000.i2c failed with error -16"

Signed-off-by: Priyanka Jain <Priyanka.Jain@freescale.com>
Change-Id: I3acf116fb4d44cc8ef8ad15849bd4a10c106a99b
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/38959
Tested-by: Review Code-CDREVIEW <CDREVIEW@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Stuart Yoder <stuart.yoder@freescale.com>
[Original patch extracted from FSL LS2085 SDK EAR5.0,
Layerscape2-SDK-SOURCE-20150828-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Jiang Lu <lu.jiang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2085a-qds.dts | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2085a-qds.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2085a-qds.dts
index 76452d4..4a1aa4c 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2085a-qds.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-ls2085a-qds.dts
@@ -54,15 +54,15 @@
 };
 
 &i2c1 {
-	status = "okay";
+	status = "disabled";
 };
 
 &i2c2 {
-	status = "okay";
+	status = "disabled";
 };
 
 &i2c3 {
-	status = "okay";
+	status = "disabled";
 };
 
 &dspi {
